id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530465\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530465\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 04, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104nxh1665703136771.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nxh1665703136771.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nxh1665703136771.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"nxh1665703136771\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"nxh1665703136771__uxput_412131\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Copy field data from the specified program buffer to the I/O buffer.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"nxh1665703136771__topic_d124991e1_d124992e1_d124993e1\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104nxh1665703136771_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"nxh1665703136771__codeblock_ikt_2rl_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">int uxput (unsigned char*buffer, shortlen);</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"nxh1665703136771__topic_d88077e1_d88078e1_d88079e1_d88080e1_d88081e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d115466e61\">Parameters</h2>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"nxh1665703136771__parml_usj_grl_bwb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">buffer</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Pointer to a program buffer containing the data to be copied to the I/O\n                  buffer.</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">len</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Number of bytes to be copied from <var class=\"keyword varname\">buffer</var> to the I/O buffer.\n                  Use a negative number to indicate that you want to copy more data.</dd>\n</dl>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"nxh1665703136771__topic_d88082e1_d88083e1_d88084e1_d88085e1_d88086e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d115466e93\">\n                       \n Return Values\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nxh1665703136771__d5976e20\">When used by a 3GL function that is performed from the formatToDbms trigger, <code class=\"ph codeph\">uxput</code> and <code class=\"ph codeph\">uxputc</code> return the values shown in the table. Otherwise, these functions return zero.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"nxh1665703136771__d5976e29\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Values returned by uxput and uxputc</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"nxh1665703136771__d5976e29__entry__1\">\nValue\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"nxh1665703136771__d5976e29__entry__2\">\nMeaning\n</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nxh1665703136771__d5976e29__entry__1\">\n1\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nxh1665703136771__d5976e29__entry__2\">There is more data in the buffer to be copied to the I/O buffer (returned when a negative length was specified).\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nxh1665703136771__d5976e29__entry__1\">\n0\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nxh1665703136771__d5976e29__entry__2\">\nSuccessful. All data\nhas been copied.\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nxh1665703136771__d5976e29__entry__1\">\n&lt;0\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nxh1665703136771__d5976e29__entry__2\">\nAn error\nhas occurred.\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"nxh1665703136771__topic_d88087e1_d88088e1_d88089e1_d88090e1_d88091e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d115466e163\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nxh1665703136771__d5947e20\">Library:  <span class=\"ph filepath\">yrtl</span>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"nxh1665703136771__topic_d88092e1_d88093e1_d88094e1_d88095e1_d88096e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d115466e176\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nxh1665703136771__p_d125015e1_d125016e1_d125017e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uxput</code> copies the specified amount\n            of field data from the specified program buffer to the I/O buffer. The data should be in\n            DBMS-specific format. Use a negative length to indicate you intend to copy more data. In\n            that case, the function will return 1, and you should call <code class=\"ph codeph\">uxputc</code> to\n            provide additional data.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nxh1665703136771__p_d125018e1_d125019e1_d125020e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">uxput</code> and <code class=\"ph codeph\">uxputc</code> should be called only by code performed or activated from the formatToDbms trigger, to provide newly encrypted data for the field in question. If called via another trigger, these functions will return zero, and perform no action.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"nxh1665703136771__note_N10088_N10067_N10016_N10001\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> When processing data moving from\n      and to Uniface components, keep in mind that the subfield separator and profile characters are\n      represented by unique characters. For more information, see the \"Subfield Separator and\n      Profile Characters\" topic.</div>\n<p class=\"p\">The following example, performed by the formatToDbms trigger of a\n            6-character string field, replaces the contents of that field by asterisks:</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104nxh1665703136771_html_1\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"nxh1665703136771__codeblock_xmb_srl_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">#include &lt;h3gl.h&gt;\nEXPORT void nullify ()\n{\n(void)uxput(\"******\", 6);\n}</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pan1665702658270.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Subfield Separator and Profile Characters</a><p>Uniface uses part of the reserved area of each meta character set (that is, the first 32 characters plus the last character) to store characters with special meaning within Uniface, such as subfield separators and profile characters.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fir1665703136962.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>uxputc</a><p>Copy additional field data from the specified program buffer to the I/O buffer.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530465\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530465\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "uxput Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 04, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Copy field data from the specified program buffer to the I/O buffer. Explain this code int uxput (unsigned char*buffer, shortlen); Copy Parameters buffer Pointer to a program buffer containing the data to be copied to the I/O buffer. len Number of bytes to be copied from buffer to the I/O buffer. Use a negative number to indicate that you want to copy more data. Return Values When used by a 3GL function that is performed from the formatToDbms trigger, uxput and uxputc return the values shown in the table. Otherwise, these functions return zero. Table 1. Values returned by uxput and uxputc Value Meaning 1 There is more data in the buffer to be copied to the I/O buffer (returned when a negative length was specified). 0 Successful. All data has been copied. <0 An error has occurred. Use Library: yrtl Description uxput copies the specified amount of field data from the specified program buffer to the I/O buffer. The data should be in DBMS-specific format. Use a negative length to indicate you intend to copy more data. In that case, the function will return 1, and you should call uxputc to provide additional data. uxput and uxputc should be called only by code performed or activated from the formatToDbms trigger, to provide newly encrypted data for the field in question. If called via another trigger, these functions will return zero, and perform no action. Note: When processing data moving from and to Uniface components, keep in mind that the subfield separator and profile characters are represented by unique characters. For more information, see the \"Subfield Separator and Profile Characters\" topic. The following example, performed by the formatToDbms trigger of a 6-character string field, replaces the contents of that field by asterisks: Explain this code #include <h3gl.h> EXPORT void nullify () { (void)uxput(\"******\", 6); } Copy Related Links Subfield Separator and Profile Characters Uniface uses part of the reserved area of each meta character set (that is, the first 32 characters plus the last character) to store characters with special meaning within Uniface, such as subfield separators and profile characters. uxputc Copy additional field data from the specified program buffer to the I/O buffer. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}